As many of you know, we have been running the much loved local pub, The White Bear, since 2021.
The last few months have brought some personal challenges. This has, understandably, had an impact on the day-to-day running of the pub.
Because of this, our agreement with Marston’s Brewery is coming to an end. Therefore we will no longer be operating The White Bear as of 18th September 2025. The brewery has decided to bring in new management and thats exactly what is needed.
We would like to take this opportunity to thank each and every one of you who’s supported the pub along the way — whether you’ve popped in for a quiet pint, celebrated special occasions, or simply made The White Bear part of your routine.
It’s been a genuine pleasure serving this community.

I’m moving!! I know this post is little late to but been so busy and not had proper time to do this which is wrong on my behalf 😔
As most of my clients know I will be starting university in September and will be studying and still working but will be around this and I have really good clients that understand and have been absolutely amazing in accommodating me and my schedule and what’s to come. 
I will soon be based in Lime Tree House which is only 5 minutes from Alloa town centre, it offers lots of parking and a private 1-1 salon space!
I will be in the new premises from the 21st July but officially working 24th July. I know I have some clients in before the 24th but don’t worry that will not change 
We will be working my usual days of Thursday, Friday and sat but will change in September. 
I will repeat again I cannot thank my clients enough as none of this would be possible without you lovely lot 💕 I’m truly thankful to you 💖
I’m looking forward to welcoming clients old and new to the new space and the next step of my journey! 
I will also still be working on the salon to in between the times I am not to bring it to what I am looking for so please bear with me at this time.

column15:
The team at Duchy Defibrillators recently moved into a new unit that is better suited to their requirements and we have been asked to support them with a few alterations. 
The first - altering the existing lights with the workshop, ground floor office and storage area. The lights are all LED already, but the location of the switches and how they were laid out, didn't work for them. 
So to make life easier, we have added these wireless receivers to each fitting, and then paired them to the wireless light switches at more suitable locations. 
A simple fix, but makes the world of difference to them. 
More bits coming up as well 🥰

column15:
We’re Moving!
I mentioned this in a story a couple of weeks ago… but now the contract is signed, sealed, and official! 🎉
I’ve been looking to upsize for over a year now. I poured my heart into trying to get Creffield- but I got abliterates at auction. At the time I was gutted, but now I realise that falling through was the biggest blessing… because it meant I could buy our farmhouse. Everything really does happen for a reason.
So naturally, after that, the bar was set very high for our new clinic space, there were a lot of boxes to tick.

Glenluiart will soon be reopening under new management, and we wish the new owners all the very best as they begin their journey here — we’re sure this magical place will continue to bring joy to many more.

New location for EleganceAesthetics! I am still based in Lydney however, I have moved from Twinfinity to which I was before. Once you have booked an appointment and have paid a deposit, the new address will be sent via message. This transition has been made due to my pregancy. 
Can’t wait to see you all and meet new faces🖤💉

So, Harv’s Auto Repairs has some very exciting news! 
As a lot of you know since we moved to our Bishops Lydeard site the growth of our business has exposed beyond belief and as a result of this we have outgrown our current unit, which means Harv’s is on the move again, but this time not very far just across the road on the same industrial estate. 
Our new site will be able to offer class 4 and class 7 MOT’s which will be housed in the small unit, so we can accommodate all the large class 7 vehicles and all campervans/motorhomes, not just for MOT’s but for servicing as well!
The bigger unit will house our service and repair workshop.

Faded Skin is moving to a new location!😭🫶🏽✨
This journey means everything to me. It has been built from the ground up, no handouts! Just hard work, prayer, dedication, graft, and God! Reaching this milestone on my own hits differently, and I’m honestly so proud of how far things have come. Massive shout out to my parents for letting me take over their space all these years, they can have it back now 🤣… As for a traditional shop; it’s never really been part of the plan, at least not right now. My focus is on continuing to invest in high-quality, medical-grade equipment and advanced technology to elevate the level of service I provide. Client safety and treatment quality are incredibly close to my heart, especially because I’ve experienced firsthand what negligence can do. That’s why every step I take is with intention. To create a space that’s safe, professional, and rooted in care.
From the 5th of August onwards, all appointments will be held at our new space: 
📍40 Martell Road, SE218EN 
I can’t wait to welcome you all to the new spot and continue growing together!🫶🏽

We've just got the keys to 7 Boroughgate. Otley is a place my grandparents used to take me and my brother on market days sometimes or if I'd pulled a sickie from school I tagged along with them to get their 'fridge bits'. It's got a great buzz about it, and it's just a stunning place to be.
I'm buzzing to be a part of the Otley community, we've called in at some amazing places already and I'm looking forward to getting to know more soon! 
Can't wait to get started getting things wrong in a new place! It's the first time we've actually taken out a large scary loan in order to facilitate a new venture so you better come!!
What you've got to look forward to? Just nice coffee and freshly prepared food from local suppliers, yes you can get that in literally dozens of other places in Otley, but somehow this will work!! I don't think anyone is as socially awkward as us, this leads to bizarre conversations that you won't get elsewhere I reckon.
Not sure when we're opening yet, hopefully within a month cos it's costing a lot of money and I've not slept properly in some time.
Keep you posted

Forthcoming Office Move
In order to manage ongoing and sustainable growth Simpler Law, alongside other companies in the HAIG Legal Group, will be moving to larger premises in August. 
Having only relocated to our current offices three years ago, increasing staff numbers and workload means that we no longer have the space for further expansion. Room is not just required for new employees but also to accommodate the necessity for more secure storage space.
We are not going to be moving far however; our new offices are a mere three minute drive from our current headquarters. We will have 67% more floor space, with room for over 140 staff, and enough parking for everyone.
We will be leaving our current offices on Friday 15th August 2025 and starting work at our new location on Monday 18th August 2025. Please bear with us over this period.
What with HAIG Legal Group also having offices in Manchester and Leicester, we have chosen to set up a centralised postal address to make life easier for all our clients. Please note our new address: Simpler Law, PO Box 1438, Lincoln LN5 5AX. Our phone number remains 0333 600 1000.

Bringing the Spirit of Thailand to Doncaster 🇹🇭
Dear friends,
I’m incredibly excited to share some wonderful news with you all!
This coming September 2025, I’ll be opening my brand-new business:
Mol Thai Therapy – Massage & Spa, located in Cavendish Court, Doncaster.
This new chapter is very close to my heart. My dream is to bring the experience of Thailand—its warmth, healing traditions, and rich culture—to people here in the UK.
At Mol Thai Therapy, you’ll be able to enjoy a variety of authentic Thai massage treatments and soothing Thai spa experiences—designed to relax your body, calm your mind, and lift your spirit.
As many of you may know, Traditional Thai Massage (Nuad Thai) was officially recognised by UNESCO in 2019 for its cultural and historical importance. It’s a proud part of our Thai heritage, and I’m so happy to be able to share it with you.
🌿 I’d be truly grateful if you could support me by following my page:
👉 Mol Thai Therapy Massage (on Facebook)
Thank you so much for your love, support, and encouragement. I can’t wait to welcome you soon!
With love,
Narumol Dudek

Hey everyone, we have some exciting news about the future of Onyx. WE ARE MOVING! On the 16th August the lease on our current premises ends, and we decided it was time for a new chapter in the Onyx story. The studio will no longer be based in Walsall. 🏡✨ Last week we moved into our new studio workshop space in EX2 at @excelsiorlondon — and it already feels like home.
We started out in a small home-based workshop, building furniture one piece at a time with reclaimed wood and a whole lot of passion.
Now, we’re stepping into something bigger — more space and more room to grow. 
Huge thank you to @excelsiorlondon , @therepublicofparkroyal and  @parkroyaldesigndistrict for giving small creative businesses like ours the chance to grow. Your support and affordable space made this move possible — we’re so grateful to be part of this amazing community.
And a big thanks to @pow_workshops for helping us find this space. We’re so glad we found you.
Being surrounded by such passionate, inspiring people makes all the difference — and we can’t wait to keep building, creating, and sharing what’s next.

We have some exciting news to share!
We're excited to announce that we are officially expanding our shop! 
After acquiring the property next door, we are extending our space across both units. This significant expansion will more than double the size of our store, and we will also be introducing a cozy mini coffee shop that will serve delightful beverages and a selection of delicious cakes.
The construction and renovation efforts are underway, and we anticipate completion by late September. We will keep you updated on our progress! More exciting updates! We will also be reopening on weekends, allowing you to stop by for a coffee, a slice of cake, and to explore the shop without having to rush on a break from work. Our new offerings will expand to include a selection of luxury interiors, soft furnishings, new home fragrance collections, and an even broader array of gifts and seasonal items.
Work is currently underway in both units; however, we remain open for business, so please feel free to stop by and browse. As we approach completion, there will be a brief shutdown to finalise the remaining tasks, but we will keep you updated on the specific dates.
We want to say a huge thank you to all our customers and supporters this wouldn't have been possible without you ! Who's ready for a big launch event?

After 8 incredible years of helping bodies move, heal, and thrive, Fruition Osteopathy has officially relocated to a brand new home — **Sculpt Fitness HQ in Newcastle**! 🏋️‍♂️✨
This move marks a bold and exciting new chapter for our clinic. Sculpt is more than just a gym — it’s a vibrant, supportive community built around strength, movement, and transformation. We’re thrilled to be part of this dynamic space, where health and performance go hand in hand.
Whether you’re an elite athlete, a weekend warrior, or simply someone who wants to feel and function better, Fruition Osteopathy continues to offer the same expert care, tailored treatment, and holistic approach that’s helped thousands of patients across the North East.

Exciting News from The Maypole Inn!
Hello everyone! 👋
My name is Luke, and I’m proud to introduce myself as the new owner of The Maypole Inn. It's a real honour to take on such a well-loved pub with so much local history and character. I want you to know that I don’t intend to ignore the past — in fact, I hope to build on the legacy that makes The Maypole so special.
